<ol><li>The tip of the pen is&nbsp;<b>dragged across all the bars</b>&nbsp;at even speed.</li><li>The photo diode&nbsp;<b>measures the intensity of the light</b>&nbsp;reflected back.</li><li>Dark bars absorb light and white spaces reflect light, so the&nbsp;<b>voltage waveform genrated</b>&nbsp;by the photo diode can be used to measure the <b>widths of bars and spaces</b>&nbsp;in the barcode.</li><li>The waveform is&nbsp;<b>converted from analogue to digital</b>.</li></ol>